cooked chicken.

18:08.035 --> 18:10.871
- I am starved.
- Use the mitts. It's hot.

18:11.038 --> 18:14.291
Stan, I'm an alien.
My skin is naturally...

18:14.458 --> 18:17.837
Damn it, Roger. I warned you.
You should have listened. I told you...

18:18.003 --> 18:21.840
You're right. You were totally right.
Curse my damnable pride.

18:22.006 --> 18:25.135
Wait. I was just about to say,
"I told you so"...

18:25.301 --> 18:30.098
...but you completely disarmed me
with a simple admission of your error.

18:30.265 --> 18:32.642
A pre-emptive strike. Of course.

18:32.809 --> 18:34.310
- Where are you going?
- India.

18:34.477 --> 18:37.980
India? But what are we supposed to do
for food?

18:43.527 --> 18:46.446
A girl at the bank told me
about this place.

18:48.739 --> 18:51.075
Okay, children, pay attention...

18:51.242 --> 18:53.703
...because you need to learn English
to survive.

18:53.870 --> 18:58.541
Repeat after me: Thank you for calling
Apple tech support.

18:58.749 --> 19:00.960
Thank you for calling
Apple tech support.

19:02.794 --> 19:08.884
There's the bell. I'll see all of you
who don't die of cholera, tomorrow at 8.

19:15.724 --> 19:17.975
Francine, I finally found you.

19:18.142 --> 19:21.312
- Stan, what are you doing here?
- I've come to take you home.

19:21.478 --> 19:23.355
This is my home now, Stan.

19:23.522 --> 19:28.193
I've found redemption here by devoting
my life to the neediest of the needy.

19:28.360 --> 19:30.486
This is my son, Sanget.

19:30.653 --> 19:35.116
I adopted him after his mother died
while toiling to feed her family.

19:35.283 --> 19:41.289
Her final wish was that I would take care
of her poor, orphaned child.

19:42.707 --> 19:45.334
You don't understand.
I was wrong and you were right...

19:45.500 --> 19:48.920
...about that blind date. Terrible.
Bullock ended up killing Melinda...

19:49.087 --> 19:52.674
...so I framed you because I didn't
wanna hear you say, "I told you so."

19:52.841 --> 19:53.925
What?

19:54.092 --> 19:57.012
I've admitted I was wrong.
I took the wind out of your sails.

19:57.178 --> 19:59.388
So come on, let's go home.
All is forgiven.

19:59.555 --> 20:01.057
You bastard!

20:04.602 --> 20:07.980
Oh, God. It's like being in a sauna
with Michael Chiklis.

20:08.147 --> 20:10.815
You made me think I was a murderer?

20:10.982 --> 20:15.028
Do you have any idea what a nightmare
you put me through?

20:15.195 --> 20:18.073
I prayed to a fricking elephant!

20:18.239 --> 20:21.117
How am I gonna explain that to Jesus?

20:21.284 --> 20:23.286
I'm sorry.

20:23.453 --> 20:25.371
You are sorry?

20:25.537 --> 20:29.166
Do you know
what super-diarrhea is, Stan?

20:29.333 --> 20:33.087
Do you know how much
you screwed up my life?

20:33.253 --> 20:35.881
I know I've done some terrible things,
but I'll fix it.

20:36.048 --> 20:37.758
I'll fix it everything, I swear.

20:37.925 --> 20:40.927
What about Sanget?
I don't want an Indian baby.

20:41.094 --> 20:45.556
I don't even like Indian food.
What are you gonna do to fix this?

20:51.354 --> 20:53.772
We won't have to worry about
that baby any more.

20:53.939 --> 20:57.275
That's right. Now you've cleared
the brush, we can build a sandbox...

20:57.442 --> 21:00.278
...where Avery Jr. Can play safely.

21:00.445 --> 21:02.781
We won't be working
any more late nights, sir?

21:02.948 --> 21:06.492
I don't know about you, Smith, but
some of us have families to go home to.

21:06.659 --> 21:09.537
Yes, I do. Yes, I do.

21:09.703 --> 21:12.498
- I'm pretty eager to get home myself.
- Don't touch me.

21:12.665 --> 21:14.834
- Still not there yet?
- Not even close.

21:50.908 --> 21:52.994
[ENGLISH]
